      "description": "Offering a mechanically sound 2002 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This unit utilizes six individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system for optimized volumetric efficiency. Power is routed through a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox to a variable M-differential lock. The chassis has undergone subframe reinforcement to mitigate common fatigue points, and the suspension geometry remains true with refreshed polyurethane bushings. While the exterior and interior show minor patina consistent with a well-loved driver, the powertrain remains robust with a linear power band and crisp throttle response. A technically sorted example for the discerning enthusiast.",
